    <name>
      <text>Expressing a whole numbers in index form</text>
    </name>
    <questiontext format="moodle_auto_format">
      <text><![CDATA[<p>Write the number \({@number@}\) in index form.</p>
<p><b>Note:</b>Your answer should be written as \(a^b\).</p>

<p>[[input:ans1]] [[validation:ans1]] [[feedback:prt1]]</p>]]></text>
    </questiontext>
    <generalfeedback format="moodle_auto_format">
      <text><![CDATA[<h3>Worked Solution</h3>

<p>The number given is \({@number@}\).</p>

<p>We check if it can be written as repeated multiplication of the same base.</p>

<p>\({@number@} = {@base@} \times {@base@} \times \dots \times {@base@} \ \ ({@exp@} \ \ \text  times) \)</p>

<p>Therefore, the index form is 
\[
{@base@}^{@exp@}.
\]
</p>]]></text>
    </generalfeedback>
